 Alhaji Jafaru Ahmed-Gwarzo, the Senior Special Assistant (SSA), Sanitation Vanguards to Gov. Abdullahi Ganduje, has called for the reintroduction of sanitary inspectors in the country to tackle environmental sanitation challenges. Ahmed-Gwarzo told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Kano on Friday that the reintroduction of sanitary inspectors was necessary in order to ensure that houses and surrounding compounds were kept clean and tidy. According to Ganduje’s SSA, the sanitary inspectors, who normally carry out house-to-house sanitary inspection, would ensure that all houses, especially in rural areas have toilet facilities to discourage indiscriminate open defecation. Continue reading Ganduje’s aide calls for reintroduction of sanitary inspectors at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard Kano State Government said it had so far employed no fewer than 4,902 people as Sanitary Inspectors as part of efforts to address various environmental sanitation challenges in the state. Alhaji Jafaru Ahmed-Gwarzo, the Senior Special Assistant, Sanitation Vanguards to the governor, disclosed this in an interview with the News… April 23, 2019 In "News" Tribune Online Open defecation: Plateau homeowners get 30-day ultimatum to build sanitary facilities PLATEAU Environmental Protection and Sanitation Agency (PEPSA) has given homeowners 30-day ultimatum to build sanitary facilities or be prosecuted. The General Manager of the agency, Mr Gabriel Bako, disclosed this in an interview with the News Agency… July 16, 2019 In "News" The Environmental Health Officers Association of Nigeria (EHOAN) has called on governments at all levels to be proactive in striving to stem Open Defecation in the country. The EHOAN Regisrar, Dr Akin Akingbehin, made the call in an interview with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Saturday in Lagos.… July 6, 2019 In "News"